KUNA : Bus accident in north-east India leaves 27 dead
NEW DELHI, May 31 (KUNA) -- At least 27 people died in India's north-eastern state of Assam on Tuesday morning, when the bus they were travelling fell into a deep gorge, reported the New Delhi Television (NDTV). The ill-fated bus was carrying the dead to a marriage party. Among the victims was the bridegroom. Meanwhile, the death toll is expected to rise further as eight passengers have been taken to a nearby hospital, and some of them are said to be in a critical condition. A total of 27 dead bodies could be recovered from the site of the accident, and rescue work is ongoing.(end) py.wsa KUNA 311009 May 11NNNN